
=Bio=

xtine burrough is a media artist, educator, and co-author
of Digital Foundations (New
Riders/AIGA 2009). Informed by the history of conceptual art, she uses social networking,
databases, search engines, blogs, and applications in combination with popular sites
like Facebook, YouTube, or Mechanical Turk, to create web communities that promote
interpretation and autonomy. xtine believes art shapes social experiences by mediating
consumer culture with rebellious practices. As an educator, she bridges the gap between
histories, theories, and production in design and new media education. 

